radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is abnormally dilated inflamed, with appendicular stranding suggestive of micro perforation. There are 2 hypodensities in segment IV of the liver measuring 1.2 x 1.2 cm that statistically represent hemangiomas. No evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation, normal gallbladder, normal pancreas, spleen, kidneys, and urinary structures. The distal ureters and bladder are unremarkable. There is no retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy.
